snippet.textDisplay:
I remember when I first rolled into my highschool parking lot in my '88 TII. That had a Turbonetics 62-1 on a rather large street port and ended up making around 420 to the rear wheels at 16psi (it was also wired by a dipshit 15 year old and died every day during classes so I had to have a friend jump me every day), and I thought there actually couldn't be a faster car on the planet. In a DFW suburb where most loud & fast cars were Mustangs or Fbodies, people were like, "THE FUCK IS THAT?" Been watching this build for a long time now and THIS video got me straight up emotional. Obviously this is a much bigger stage with a historical - let's be real, it will ultimately be legendary - build in the rotary community, but all of you who have put your heart and soul into whatever it is you might have built and then been able to share it with friends, family and even people you otherwise might not get along with know exactly how Rob was feeling right then.
/novella
Fucking sick, Mr. Dahm. Can't wait to see (and will patiently wait because the good things in life take time as you of all people know) and hear this thing doing 1/2 miles & beyond. I WANT A ROTARY AGAIN!!!
